cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with learning visual representations from videos for action recognition, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses unsupervised learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
